WEBVTT

00:01.610 --> 00:04.400
<i>A detective is like an ocean wave.</i>

00:06.150 --> 00:09.510
<i>The criminal works so hard 
to build a sandcastle,</i>

00:09.510 --> 00:11.370
<i>then he comes in at the end</i>

00:11.370 --> 00:12.510
<i>and washes it all away.</i>

00:18.450 --> 00:22.520
<i>A wave is neither good nor evil.
Neither compassionate nor cruel.</i>

00:23.020 --> 00:27.300
<i>It simply returns everything 
to its natural state.</i>

00:31.860 --> 00:35.010
"Killed Again, Mr. Detective?"

02:17.570 --> 02:19.840
<i>And if a detective is an ocean wave,</i>

02:19.840 --> 02:23.230
<i>then that man is a giant tsunami 
that swallows up the whole beach.</i>

02:23.970 --> 02:28.580
<i>No matter the case, he'll solve it, 
smash it into nothingness, and end it.</i>

02:29.220 --> 02:31.500
<i>The greatest detective in history...</i>

02:31.500 --> 02:35.460
m 0 0 l 100 0 100 100 0 100

02:31.500 --> 02:35.460
The Murder of 66 Police Officers — Killer Arrested

02:31.500 --> 02:35.460
The European Euro Robbery — Hiding Spot Found

02:31.500 --> 02:35.460
The Kingdom of Vanrecht Mass Disappearance Case

02:31.500 --> 02:35.460
— Solved by the Immortal Detective

02:31.500 --> 02:35.460
The Seven Continents Great Romance Incident

02:31.500 --> 02:35.460
— Empress Captured by Famous Detective

02:31.500 --> 02:35.460
Another Success for Outsuki Tatsuya — Cannibal Cult Arrested

02:32.180 --> 02:33.620
<i>Outsuki Tatsuya.</i>

02:36.340 --> 02:39.660
<i>And I'm his son, Outsuki Sakuya.</i>

02:40.180 --> 02:42.410
m 0 0 l 100 0 100 100 0 100

02:40.180 --> 02:42.410
Father.
By the time you read this, I will be gone from this world.
I don't have any real memories of you trying to raise me,
 but thanks anyway.

02:43.430 --> 02:43.520
<b>Will</b>

02:43.520 --> 02:43.600
<b>Will</b>

02:43.600 --> 02:49.980
<b>Will</b>

02:44.980 --> 02:49.980
Logical and fair. 
And just the right degree of tear-jerking.

02:50.700 --> 02:54.260
<i>Why am I writing a will, you ask? 
It's something I do every day.</i>

02:54.690 --> 03:00.150
<b>Outsuki</b>

02:54.690 --> 03:00.150
<b>Detective</b>

02:54.690 --> 03:00.150
<b>Agency</b>

02:55.490 --> 03:00.150
<i>If I had to give a reason, it's because 
my shoelace snapped suddenly today.</i>

03:00.660 --> 03:04.270
<i>Or maybe it's because 
a black cat crossed my path.</i>

03:20.860 --> 03:25.220
Sakuya-sama, everyone else 
has already gone to meet the client.

03:25.810 --> 03:27.980
B-Before we talk about that,

03:27.980 --> 03:33.020
could you perhaps tell me 
why you were sniffing my uniform?

03:33.550 --> 03:34.620
I did no such thing.

03:34.620 --> 03:35.900
You totally did!

03:36.430 --> 03:41.110
Does my scent just drive 
the ladies wild or something?

03:41.490 --> 03:42.240
It does not.

03:44.900 --> 03:46.620
I assumed as such.

03:46.620 --> 03:53.080
If it did, school would be a lot more fun.

03:53.080 --> 03:58.840
So you're saying you find school boring?
 Is that <i>really</i> the case?

03:58.840 --> 03:59.840
Huh?

04:00.470 --> 04:03.920
It would appear that you 
once again spent time

04:03.920 --> 04:06.830
with an attractive school nurse
 in her late 20s.

04:07.230 --> 04:10.060
Your time at school 
seems quite enjoyable to me.

04:11.150 --> 04:13.650
Wh-What are you talking about?

04:14.010 --> 04:18.060
I can smell disinfectant and medicine,

04:18.060 --> 04:21.480
plus the faint whiff of perfume
 on your uniform.

04:22.680 --> 04:25.780
The medicine smell no doubt 
came from the nurse's office.

04:27.050 --> 04:30.970
And the perfume is from 
the new Vivi Alice spring line.

04:31.870 --> 04:35.250
It's pricier than a high school
 student could afford.

04:35.250 --> 04:36.660
You've got it wrong.

04:37.080 --> 04:39.420
I scraped my leg in gym class.

04:39.420 --> 04:43.510
A-And I couldn't just ignore it
 with all my classmates watching.

04:43.980 --> 04:45.840
You know what I mean, right?

04:46.360 --> 04:49.620
The nurse got really worried 
when she saw the scrape,

04:49.620 --> 04:52.240
and started giving me 
a full-body examination.

04:52.240 --> 04:57.750
Yes, she was just doing her job, 
nothing more. Nothing bad at all.

04:59.880 --> 05:04.490
Those last two sentences make it clear 
something inappropriate happened.

05:05.400 --> 05:08.410
I can't hide anything from you,
 huh, Lilithea?

05:08.410 --> 05:11.000
So you admit your guilt?

05:11.320 --> 05:13.590
Seriously, though. Nothing happened.

05:14.030 --> 05:17.700
I have a duty to keep an eye
 on you at all times,

05:17.700 --> 05:20.520
and to make sure 
you don't act inappropriately.

05:22.510 --> 05:27.310
After all... I <i>am</i> 
Detective Sakuya's assistant.

05:29.110 --> 05:31.930
I'm happy you're calling me "Detective,"

05:32.350 --> 05:36.120
but my dad has never viewed me
 as a full-fledged sleuth.

05:40.910 --> 05:41.870
In that case...

05:44.030 --> 05:48.410
The two of us together 
will be one "full-fledged sleuth."

05:59.230 --> 05:59.960
Where's my dad?

06:00.490 --> 06:05.080
Tatsuya-sama just left for the airport
 on an emergency call.

06:05.410 --> 06:07.650
There's been a hijacking.

06:07.650 --> 06:09.050
A hijacking?

06:09.050 --> 06:15.620
The hijacked passenger plane was coming
to Japan from Singapore's Changi Airport.

06:16.050 --> 06:18.390
The hijacker is a nine-year old girl.

06:19.410 --> 06:24.760
She's taken 179 passengers and crew
 hostage aboard the aircraft.

06:24.760 --> 06:26.110
Nine years old?

06:27.000 --> 06:29.040
<i>If they called for my dad,</i>

06:29.040 --> 06:34.230
<i>that means they think only Outsuki 
Tatsuya can resolve the situation.</i>

06:37.000 --> 06:40.050
The hijacked plane was...

06:41.240 --> 06:44.040
flight XX999.

06:45.610 --> 06:46.760
Thank you.

06:47.190 --> 06:49.410
By the way, what's on 
my schedule for the day?

06:49.410 --> 06:51.360
An adultery investigation.

06:51.360 --> 06:53.970
Nice. Seems safe.

06:55.260 --> 07:00.020
I think it would be better for you to be
 a bit more ambitious, Sakuya-sama.

07:00.020 --> 07:03.310
You think a detective should be 
trying to solve bigger cases?

07:03.890 --> 07:06.340
A locked-room murder 
in a mansion somewhere?

07:06.340 --> 07:09.570
A killing spree on an isolated island?

07:10.420 --> 07:12.140
I'd rather not.

07:15.320 --> 07:18.000
So who's the target for today?

07:18.990 --> 07:21.840
Katsuragi Makoto, age 43.

07:21.840 --> 07:24.220
He works for a film distribution company,

07:24.220 --> 07:27.420
and is responsible for 
a number of hit movies.

07:28.090 --> 07:28.970
Your mission...

07:30.180 --> 07:34.930
is to tail him aboard the Queen Irie
bound for Singapore from Yokohama.

07:35.910 --> 07:40.830
The Queen Irie Murder Case, Part 1

07:42.810 --> 07:44.390
It's huge.

07:44.970 --> 07:52.280
The Queen Irie is Japan's largest cruise liner,
with a passenger capacity of 1,100.

07:58.710 --> 08:00.290
Shall I carry those for you?

08:00.290 --> 08:03.170
No, thanks. I can do it myself.

08:03.170 --> 08:04.220
Is that...

08:04.620 --> 08:05.790
Katsuragi Makoto.

08:17.500 --> 08:21.060
He's occasionally been known 
to purchase suspicious items,

08:21.060 --> 08:24.860
and has started renting a condo
 in downtown Tokyo.

08:25.650 --> 08:29.730
He had an awful lot of luggage with him.
Wonder what was inside.

08:29.730 --> 08:34.630
Presents for a girl? Adult toys 
he can't tell anybody about?

08:34.630 --> 08:35.530
Disgusting.

08:36.590 --> 08:39.240
Would it kill you to make 
a <i>proper</i> hypothesis for once?

08:40.780 --> 08:43.670
What's he doing on this ship, anyway?

08:43.670 --> 08:44.540
It's for a movie.

08:45.250 --> 08:53.760
<b>Past Appearances</b>

08:45.250 --> 08:53.760
<b>Television</b>

08:45.250 --> 08:53.760
<b>The XYZ Murders
Attendant</b>

08:45.250 --> 08:53.760
<b>Commercials</b>

08:45.250 --> 08:53.760
<b>Taiyou Ham</b>

08:45.430 --> 08:50.630
They're interviewing the main actress
 aboard this cruise ship.

08:50.630 --> 08:53.240
It's a joint promotion 
with some travel company.

08:53.760 --> 08:56.120
Haigamine Yuriu?

08:56.600 --> 08:59.970
She's a new actress who was 
specially chosen to appear in this movie.

08:59.970 --> 09:03.290
You're right. She's barely
appeared in anything.

09:04.850 --> 09:09.820
Outsuki Tatsuya

09:04.850 --> 09:09.820
<b>Jumping aboard now.
\h10,000 meters up.
\h\h\h\hReally high!</b>

09:06.300 --> 09:09.410
You and your father have 
very different tendencies.

09:10.150 --> 09:12.310
I use him as an example
 of what not to do.

09:12.780 --> 09:15.740
<b>Read</b>

09:12.780 --> 09:15.740
<b>Just don't slip and fall off
It'll annoy me</b>

09:15.740 --> 09:19.000
I know how Dad hates heights.

09:19.000 --> 09:22.020
All right. Let's get to work.

09:22.020 --> 09:22.810
Sure.

09:28.010 --> 09:32.920
Katsuragi's heading for day one's 
big event: the Queen Irie Circus.

09:33.190 --> 09:35.750
When's the last time I went to the circus?

09:35.750 --> 09:37.550
I've never been to one.

09:37.930 --> 09:40.390
I've only read about them
 in picture books.

09:41.720 --> 09:42.990
Ah, sorry.

09:45.480 --> 09:48.780
Sozorogi-san? Why are you 
on a luxury cruise ship?

09:48.780 --> 09:52.940
Vacation. My little brother
 got me tickets.

09:53.210 --> 09:54.180
Vacation?

09:54.180 --> 09:57.880
If you're here, Tatsuya-san 
must be here too, right?

09:57.880 --> 10:00.130
Don't involve me in whatever you're up to.

10:00.130 --> 10:03.670
Don't worry. My dad's on another case.

10:03.670 --> 10:05.450
Well, that's okay then.

10:05.810 --> 10:10.710
You sure have it rough, don't you? 
Having to take care of his lazy son.

10:11.020 --> 10:13.720
If you ever need a good lawyer,
 just let me know.

10:14.660 --> 10:18.150
Sakuya-sama, the performance 
is beginning soon.

10:21.470 --> 10:26.010
All right. The booze is calling to me, 
so I'll bid you a pleasant evening.

10:30.820 --> 10:35.190
<i>A detective </i>and<i> a policeman
 on the same cruise ship?</i>

10:35.940 --> 10:38.300
<i>No, I'm sure it doesn't mean anything.</i>

10:45.240 --> 10:48.510
Sakuya-sama, don't focus 
 on the performance so much

10:48.510 --> 10:51.070
that you forget about 
watching our target.

10:51.070 --> 10:55.270
Don't worry. The circus doesn't
 really interest me, anyway.

10:56.030 --> 10:58.170
It doesn't?

10:58.170 --> 11:02.440
I don't quite understand 
what I'm supposed to be enjoying.

11:39.160 --> 11:40.150
Are you okay?

11:43.740 --> 11:46.840
I should just enjoy the thrills 
instead of overthinking it.

11:48.210 --> 11:50.520
Even a little kid can do that.

11:58.820 --> 11:59.900
A pierrot?

12:00.170 --> 12:03.650
That's a clown. Pierrots cry.

12:04.360 --> 12:07.480
If it has teardrop makeup 
on its cheeks, it's a pierrot.

12:07.480 --> 12:11.000
If not, it's a clown. A jester.

12:11.470 --> 12:13.810
A jester, huh?

12:14.610 --> 12:17.250
Oh, Katsuragi-san!

12:16.070 --> 12:17.010
Nice to see you.

12:18.170 --> 12:21.140
It's so much more incredible 
in person, isn't it?

12:21.140 --> 12:24.090
Yes, I was surprised too.

12:24.510 --> 12:28.150
I'm not seeing him spending 
any time alone with a girl.

12:28.540 --> 12:31.790
He may not be committing adultery
 with a human woman.

12:33.270 --> 12:36.190
It could be with a cat, or a cactus,

12:36.570 --> 12:37.650
or an airplane?

12:39.580 --> 12:41.430
No way.

12:42.200 --> 12:45.610
<i>She's been a weird one
for as long as I've known her.</i>

12:47.480 --> 12:52.450
<i>I met Lilithea on one of my dad's cases.</i>

12:52.900 --> 12:56.370
<i>After the case, she had nowhere to go,</i>

12:56.370 --> 12:58.250
<i>so she joined our agency.</i>

13:10.140 --> 13:12.130
The Globe of Death.

13:12.130 --> 13:15.100
It says it's one of 
the biggest events in the show.

13:15.100 --> 13:19.060
<b>Globe of Death</b>

13:15.100 --> 13:19.060
<b>Globe of Death</b>

13:15.100 --> 13:19.060
Globe of Death

13:15.100 --> 13:19.060
Globe of Death

13:15.100 --> 13:19.060
Globe of Death

13:15.420 --> 13:19.060
They ride around in that globe 
on motorcycles?

13:20.030 --> 13:22.090
I'd be dead in two seconds.

13:23.880 --> 13:26.020
<i>The Globe of Death, huh?</i>

13:27.510 --> 13:29.990
<b>What an awful name.</b>

13:28.170 --> 13:29.400
<i>What an awful name.</i>

13:30.140 --> 13:35.000
Killed Again,
Mr. Detective?

13:38.350 --> 13:40.780
You keep an eye on him, Lilithea.

13:41.210 --> 13:44.400
I'll go see what I can learn 
from the people he's with.

13:44.400 --> 13:45.130
Right.

13:45.130 --> 13:48.830
Don't give in to the temptation to go off
 and have fun on the cruise.

13:48.830 --> 13:50.280
I would never.

13:50.280 --> 13:50.890
No?

13:51.360 --> 13:54.590
A cruise ship at night is filled 
with all kinds of entertainment,

13:54.590 --> 13:57.640
but I would never give 
into such temptation.

13:57.640 --> 13:57.770
<b>Darts Tournament</b>

13:57.640 --> 13:57.770
<b>Making the Most of Your First Trip on
The Queen Irie
The Complete Guide</b>

