14:01.240 --> 14:01.530
<b>Darts Tournament</b>

14:01.240 --> 14:01.530
<b>Making the Most of Your First Trip on
The Queen Irie
The Complete Guide</b>

14:01.520 --> 14:02.680
This is...

14:02.680 --> 14:06.610
I-It's an assistant's job is to make sure
 she's prepared in advance.

14:08.040 --> 14:09.570
Just be careful.

14:10.210 --> 14:13.450
You too, Sakuya-sama. Take care.

14:17.740 --> 14:19.680
If Dad were here,

14:19.680 --> 14:23.870
he'd tell me to watch the guy every second
 even if it means peeing my pants.

14:31.250 --> 14:34.310
I guess it's not as easy in real life
 as it is in the movies.

14:36.510 --> 14:37.660
Are you okay?

14:38.210 --> 14:39.660
Sorry to bother you.

14:40.210 --> 14:42.530
Um... Where are we?

14:42.850 --> 14:44.320
The men's bathroom.

14:44.940 --> 14:46.530
No!

14:46.970 --> 14:49.880
Please listen! 
I've got a really good reason!

14:49.880 --> 14:52.120
Calm down. Can you stand?

14:53.080 --> 14:55.100
Th-Thank you.

14:57.710 --> 15:00.550
<b>Past Appearances</b>

14:57.710 --> 15:00.550
<b>Television</b>

14:57.710 --> 15:00.550
<b>The XYZ Murders
Attendant</b>

14:57.710 --> 15:00.550
<b>Commercials</b>

14:57.710 --> 15:00.550
<b>Taiyou Ham</b>

15:01.350 --> 15:06.240
Are you... Haigamine Yuriu-san?

15:06.240 --> 15:08.380
Yup, I'm Yuriu!

15:09.800 --> 15:10.630
Um...

15:11.160 --> 15:13.600
Are you a detective, Sakuya-san?

15:15.060 --> 15:16.970
Wh-Why do you think that?

15:17.770 --> 15:22.810
Because you said, "Watch the guy every second
 even if it means peeing my pants."

15:22.810 --> 15:26.650
Oh, uh, well, about that...

15:26.650 --> 15:29.490
Is it possible for me to hire you?

15:30.520 --> 15:31.110
Hire me?

15:31.330 --> 15:32.180
Yup!

15:35.610 --> 15:38.250
I want you to find a cat named Lulu-chan.

15:38.250 --> 15:39.320
A cat?

15:39.320 --> 15:43.920
I heard her crying in the ducts,
so I went in there to look for her.

15:44.220 --> 15:49.450
But the ceiling gave way under me 
and I fell into the men's bathroom...

15:53.830 --> 15:56.930
Sorry, I was just laughing at myself.

15:57.850 --> 16:01.820
Lulu-chan's the producer's calico cat.

16:01.820 --> 16:02.910
The producer?

16:02.910 --> 16:07.320
Right. Katsuragi-san, 
the producer for my movie.

16:07.740 --> 16:10.070
He <i>loves</i> cats.

16:10.070 --> 16:15.070
He brought them all on the cruise,
 but one ran off.

16:15.320 --> 16:18.420
So Katsuragi-san asked you
 to look for it?

16:18.420 --> 16:21.460
Nope. I took it upon myself!

16:23.030 --> 16:26.060
So you went up into the ducts 
even though he didn't ask you to?

16:26.060 --> 16:28.270
You're an unusual person, aren't you?

16:28.270 --> 16:30.260
Well, I'm worried about the kitty.

16:30.690 --> 16:33.430
Will you please take the job?

16:34.380 --> 16:36.790
Fine. I'll do it.

16:37.750 --> 16:40.020
Thank you, master.

16:40.020 --> 16:43.980
I don't remember taking you
 on as an apprentice.

16:44.450 --> 16:48.740
<i>But if I get close to her, I can probably
 learn a lot about Katsuragi.</i>

16:50.170 --> 16:53.890
I'm actually playing a detective
 in my upcoming movie.

16:53.890 --> 16:58.410
My name is Uzura, 
Teenage Girl Detective!

16:59.140 --> 17:03.090
Is looking for this cat 
your way of practicing for the role?

17:03.090 --> 17:04.840
I'm embarrassed to say it, but kinda.

17:04.840 --> 17:07.630
Oh, but I <i>am</i> also worried. Really!

17:08.130 --> 17:11.710
I want my first starring role
 to be a success.

17:12.540 --> 17:16.430
I won't get in your way. 
If anything, I promise to be helpful.

17:16.670 --> 17:17.670
Please!

17:18.840 --> 17:22.100
Fine. Go for it.

17:22.100 --> 17:24.600
Thank you, master!

17:24.600 --> 17:26.380
You're welcome.

17:27.500 --> 17:30.100
Contact me immediately 
if anything comes up.

17:30.100 --> 17:30.910
Right.

17:30.910 --> 17:33.550
And don't do anything dangerous.

17:33.550 --> 17:35.310
I'll be careful.

17:35.720 --> 17:38.180
And don't you go dying on me, master.

17:38.180 --> 17:40.160
I don't see that happening.

17:40.160 --> 17:42.970
But I'm glad I have 
such a kind apprentice.

17:42.970 --> 17:46.000
"Kind"? Aw, shucks.

17:46.510 --> 17:51.780
I'm tying a bow around those words
and sending 'em right back to ya.

17:53.950 --> 17:55.930
Lulu-chan!

17:57.570 --> 18:01.260
Excuse me. Have you seen 
a calico cat around here?

18:01.260 --> 18:04.340
A calico cat? No, I haven't.

18:04.340 --> 18:05.640
I see.

18:05.990 --> 18:09.310
I sometimes see rats 
in the cargo hold up ahead.

18:09.310 --> 18:11.310
So there might be a cat there too.

18:11.740 --> 18:13.500
I'd like to go look, if I may.

18:13.940 --> 18:15.070
Go right ahead.

18:15.070 --> 18:16.890
Thank you.

18:16.890 --> 18:17.620
No problem.

18:29.250 --> 18:30.750
Lulu-chan!

18:35.010 --> 18:36.970
Lulu-chan!

18:41.260 --> 18:43.260
Lulu-chan?

18:53.270 --> 18:55.410
A Kawashima Ultra Sherba?

18:56.930 --> 18:59.990
They put them here 
when the performance is over?

19:11.300 --> 19:12.080
<i>Dead...</i>

19:12.710 --> 19:14.040
<i>He's dead?</i>

19:14.870 --> 19:15.980
<i>It's that guy.</i>

19:18.820 --> 19:21.490
Why did I have to find this body?

19:21.860 --> 19:25.350
Now that I've seen it, 
I have to get involved.

19:25.780 --> 19:28.570
I can't pretend I didn't see it.

19:34.330 --> 19:35.700
This is...

19:36.110 --> 19:38.660
They use this to lift 
and service the motorcycles?

19:42.760 --> 19:48.410
<i>He's too high up to have used
the remote control to hang himself.</i>

19:49.050 --> 19:52.390
<i>Rising a few dozen centimeters
would've been enough to choke him.</i>

19:52.790 --> 19:57.250
<i>If he'd passed out and dropped the remote,
that would've stopped it rising.</i>

20:00.270 --> 20:01.450
Hello?

20:01.450 --> 20:05.450
I have a lot to tell you. 
I'm in a cargo hold on the first floor.

20:05.450 --> 20:07.430
Something awful's happened...

20:07.810 --> 20:10.390
Huh? You're in the middle of a darts game?

20:10.390 --> 20:13.160
Are you seriously playing darts <i>now</i>?

20:13.160 --> 20:15.050
Just get down here!

20:20.020 --> 20:21.300
I think I just heard...

20:28.450 --> 20:29.990
Did it belong to the victim?

20:56.530 --> 20:57.770
<i>I can't breathe.</i>

20:59.370 --> 21:02.130
<i>Who'd do such a thing?</i>

21:03.070 --> 21:05.000
<i>That's my killer?</i>

21:05.560 --> 21:08.870
<i>Is it a he? Or a she?</i>

21:10.310 --> 21:12.680
<i>That's a pierrot.</i>

21:13.710 --> 21:14.710
<i>Damn it.</i>

21:24.260 --> 21:26.070
<i>Death is scary.</i>

21:26.620 --> 21:30.030
<i>I really hate it.</i>

21:30.770 --> 21:34.910
<i>Both my death, and other people's.</i>

21:36.520 --> 21:42.540
<i>Being a detective really is a good way
 to get yourself killed.</i>

22:11.350 --> 22:12.550
Lilithea?

22:15.160 --> 22:20.050
Killed again, Mr. Detective?

24:04.270 --> 24:10.250
Next Episode

24:04.270 --> 24:10.250
The Queen Irie Murder Case, Part 2

24:05.490 --> 24:09.960
<i>Next episode: "The Queen Irie
Murder Case, Part 2."</i>
